Most mobs hit for less then mobs in PoV. <br>
<br>
Wurms are probably the hardest things. Hit for around quad 300.<br>
Red wurms have TWO fire based AE's. Both can do max of 300.<br>
White wurms have TWO cold based AE's. One maxes at 300, other at 350. White wurms are also clerics, and will Complete Heal, cast various cleric spells, and can gate.<br>
<br>
Drakes are all fairly easy, around quad 300 on all of them... Shimmering drakes (butterfly-drakes) are druids, and can CAST (not a proc) dispel, various druid nukes/dots, and gate.<br>
Red drakes have a very weak fire AE, around 100 damage.<br>
Blue drakes are clerics, also have a single target PROC that will drain the targets HP/mana. They cast Complete Heal, various cleric nukes, and can gate.<br>
Black drakes are SK's, they will harm touch your pullers for about 750-1000. Fun. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Have a DoT AE, pretty weak.<br>
Green drakes are plain warriors. BUT they will PROC a single target slow on their target. Highly recommend a SK or Paladin tank, to keep aggro.<br>
<br>
Rancors are straight up melee, again, around quad 300.<br>
<br>
Wyverns are fun... :P<br>
A raging wyvern is very easy, quads around 300.<br>
A vehement wyvern... these, you watch out for. They quad for 350 VERY VERY quickly. They'll take out your tank FAST if you're not ready.<br>
There's another kind of wyvern, but I forgot it's name. Its not that tough though.<br>
<br>
Hide your casters around a corner, and have fun splitting the first pull of 2 mobs. :P If you get 3-4 groups, you could PROBABLY take 2 wurms at once, but it can get ugly hehe.<br>
<br>
If you have any 60+ Paladins or SK's, they can tank just fine in HoT. You'll want 1 cleric watching each, and maybe another healer for quick heals on them, until your clerics get it down. I don't think they'll have much trouble though, with them being 65. <br>
<br>
Anyone 61+ will resist most AE's VERY easily. Try to get at least 150 CR/FR on the melee. AE bard song is very very nice.<br>
<br>
ALL mobs are Magic-slowable, EXCEPT for the shimmering drakes. (Butterfly-drakes) Those are disease slowable.<br>
<br>
All mobs have pretty high MR though, Tash/Malo/OOS helps ALOT on resists. <br>
<br>
YOU MUST MANA SIEVE blue drakes, shimmering (butterfly) drakes, and white wurms. If you don't, most likely they'll gate, and summon your raid one by one. Very very messy. :P<br>
<br>
All in all, a great place to learn how to work as a guild. My guild grew up there, had some fun raids that went until 6 am local time =P<br>
<br>
If no one else is camping it, the entrance is a great spot to do so, BUT DO NOT OPEN THE DOOR WHILE YOU ARE FIGHTING! That's very important. :P<br>
<br>
Monk or SK could pull to the steps, and someone else could tag up. Not that tough, a 60+ of any class can SOMETIMES split the first pull, just by pulling the higher level wurm. It's rare, but it happens. <br>
<br>
