- Fire/Ice resists are needed mainly...but even with about 150 resists and lvl 63 you won't resist many AEs (getting it boosted by a Bard to 250+ makes a huge difference)<br>
- Corners are your friends against AE-Mobs (try to hide nukers/healers around a corner. If the wurm isnt in direct LOS, he cant hit you with AE)<br>
- Nuke hard at the end against caster Mobs (most things are). Gating Mobs = very nasty<br>
- All casters should bind themselves outside of ToV<br>
- Have a necro (or Sk if you don't have a necro) with enough coffins in ToV. This might not be needed for your first few raids, where you will probably just stand at the door where CR is easy...but once you move in deeper and wipe...<br>
- don't fight too close to HoT-door and never let *anyone* pull your corpse too close to door or they dragons outside might/will aggro.<br>
- never open HoT-door while you are fighting inside. <br>
<br>
That are the main points that came into my  mind right now...<br>
<br>
Beside that your size and levels sound more than sufficient for HoT-raids. <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
