<br>
&quot;Have a necro (or Sk if you don't have a necro) with enough coffins in ToV. This might not be needed for your first few raids, where you will probably just stand at the door where CR is easy...but once you move in deeper and wipe...&quot;<br>
<br>
I would suggest that you have a necro with a bunch of coffins the first few times as well, especially during your first few attempts. Once you get the first 2 broken, you'll start pulling from deeper in. All it takes is one mob in there to gate at low health and start summoning for your raid to wipe. If this is your first few times in, especially considering you don't have alot of 60+ tanks for rotation, you'll probably not be able to get back to that dragon to get corpses normally. Which means, of course, necro summon is required.<br>
<br>
&quot;Fire/Ice resists are needed mainly...but even with about 150 resists and lvl 63 you won't resist many AEs (getting it boosted by a Bard to 250+ makes a huge difference)&quot;<br>
<br>
Without a bard, my resists will vary from 225-260 on fire/cold/magic resists. With bard I'm consistently over 300 in these 3 area. When I am hovering around 250, I really don't notice an increase in resists across any line. Once I break 300, I start resisting fire almost all the time. Cold, however, I almost never resist even above 300. With healers that are paying attention, it's not really that big of a deal anymore but, I'm just saying I disagree with the comment above about &quot;getting it boosted by a Bard to 250+ makes a huge difference&quot;. For me at least, getting above 300 only helps on fire.<br>
<br>
